I critiqued art Pentelonus.

145
00:05:42,713 --> 00:05:44,794
Every time I was nervous, I used that word.

146
00:05:44,794 --> 00:05:47,156
And I turned into a Pokemon.

147
00:05:47,156 --> 00:05:48,417
It turned into a running gag.

148
00:05:48,417 --> 00:05:50,178
Like people just, like it was a thing.

149
00:05:50,178 --> 00:05:53,661
And the weird thing about it is it actually worked

150
00:05:53,661 --> 00:05:54,901
because I calmed down.

151
00:05:55,372 --> 00:06:02,057
And the moment I remember where I realized that was I come in in the morning, there's a designer and a coder, not even related to my team.

152
00:06:02,057 --> 00:06:04,959
They're like half dead because in the morning nobody's awake in the morning.

153
00:06:04,959 --> 00:06:07,882
They're like slurping a coffee and they don't even think and just say pantalones.

154
00:06:08,942 --> 00:06:10,323
As you know, okay, I got it.

155
00:06:10,323 --> 00:06:13,063
Like, if I can get a group of people

156
00:06:13,063 --> 00:06:15,144
randomly saying a completely random word

157
00:06:15,144 --> 00:06:17,905
to me in the morning without thinking,

158
00:06:17,905 --> 00:06:19,245
I'm actually directing.

159
00:06:19,245 --> 00:06:22,546
Like, this is, in essence, this is direction.

160
00:06:22,546 --> 00:06:24,587
So it worked out in that sense.

161
00:06:24,587 --> 00:06:27,427
And the funny thing about it is as well,

162
00:06:27,427 --> 00:06:29,368
like, it calmed me down, which was essential.

163
00:06:29,368 --> 00:06:31,069
Because I wasn't anxious anymore

164
00:06:31,069 --> 00:06:33,449
because I realized I'm here for the fun.

165
00:06:33,449 --> 00:06:34,409
I'm here to enjoy myself.

166
00:06:34,409 --> 00:06:36,770
I'm here to enjoy all of this with like,

167
00:06:37,330 --> 00:06:42,253
all the people that are in my team and it helped me to kind of accept the fact that

168
00:06:42,253 --> 00:06:48,055
it doesn't matter like it's just it's just there for the shits and the giggles right

169
00:06:48,055 --> 00:06:53,377
and so I got happy I calmed down I was like yeah this is it like this is what I want to do this is

170
00:06:53,377 --> 00:07:00,161
this is where I'm going right now and it was really interesting because as I calmed down my team

171
00:07:00,161 --> 00:07:00,601
calmed down

172
00:07:01,787 --> 00:07:07,891
So I realized something that my personal motivation actually is also the team's motivation.

173
00:07:07,891 --> 00:07:14,216
So it was like my first big lesson I had was I'm here to motivate people.

174
00:07:14,216 --> 00:07:18,719
And again, like when you're expecting to be art director, you go like, oh, I'm going to do art direction.

175
00:07:18,719 --> 00:07:20,460
I'm going to show everybody what kind of art we're going to do.

176
00:07:20,954 --> 00:07:24,095
But actually, what my first big thing was is,

177
00:07:24,095 --> 00:07:25,315
I'm here to motivate people.

178
00:07:25,315 --> 00:07:27,095
I just have to get people excited

179
00:07:27,095 --> 00:07:28,156
about the stuff we're working on.

180
00:07:28,156 --> 00:07:29,596
And I mean, it makes sense in a way.

181
00:07:29,596 --> 00:07:31,316
Imagine you're going into a meeting,

182
00:07:31,316 --> 00:07:32,917
the art director is sitting there

183
00:07:32,917 --> 00:07:34,357
and he's anxious and nervous and like,

184
00:07:34,357 --> 00:07:37,958
and the lead goes like,

185
00:07:37,958 --> 00:07:38,838
holy shit, what's going on?

186
00:07:38,838 --> 00:07:39,398
He's nervous.

187
00:07:39,398 --> 00:07:42,538
And so he gets nervous because obviously,

188
00:07:42,538 --> 00:07:44,779
if he knows probably things I don't know,

189
00:07:44,779 --> 00:07:45,859
where in my head it's like,

190
00:07:45,859 --> 00:07:47,800
I'm not ready, I'm not ready, I'm not ready.

191
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:48,480
And.

192
00:07:49,710 --> 00:07:55,152
he goes down to the artists and he's nervous because he thinks I know something he doesn't know

193
00:07:55,152 --> 00:07:58,852
and therefore he's nervous and the artist goes like oh my god my lead is nervous

194
00:07:58,852 --> 00:08:02,813
something's going on and the lead goes like I don't know I don't know I don't know I don't know

195
00:08:02,813 --> 00:08:07,134
and the artist gets nervous so like it kind of mitigates down to the team it's fascinating

196
00:08:07,134 --> 00:08:14,096
because you don't think you have that power over people but you do and so what happens is

197
00:08:14,096 --> 00:08:16,136
when you relax the opposite happens

198
00:08:16,892 --> 00:08:17,993
people calm down.

199
00:08:17,993 --> 00:08:19,855
Like, oh, my art director's chill, everything's fine,

200
00:08:19,855 --> 00:08:20,917
okay, we'll be good.

201
00:08:20,917 --> 00:08:22,699
If your art director is actually super excited

202
00:08:22,699 --> 00:08:24,782
at what you did today, you'll get excited

203
00:08:24,782 --> 00:08:26,664
because you're an artist, you want to get people excited,

204
00:08:26,664 --> 00:08:29,548
that's the nature of your job.

205
00:08:29,548 --> 00:08:32,371
So, in a way, you being happy and motivated

206
00:08:32,371 --> 00:08:33,793
actually pushes the entire team.

207
00:08:34,604 --> 00:08:37,006
And I'm mentioning this because it's so important

208
00:08:37,006 --> 00:08:38,987
to find a way to do it in a positive way

209
00:08:38,987 --> 00:08:41,008
because some people have imposter syndrome

210
00:08:41,008 --> 00:08:41,869
or something similar.

211
00:08:41,869 --> 00:08:43,069
It's for every person, it's different.

212
00:08:43,069 --> 00:08:46,892
But if you use something that's negative to kind of cover it,

213
00:08:46,892 --> 00:08:48,573
it will hit down to your team

214
00:08:48,573 --> 00:08:50,114
and it will create an atmosphere

215
00:08:50,114 --> 00:08:51,495
that is not positive and not productive.

216
00:08:51,495 --> 00:08:54,236
So it's very important, whatever your pentalonus is,

217
00:08:54,236 --> 00:08:57,298
it has to be something that enforces positivity

218
00:08:57,298 --> 00:08:59,640
because it will hit your team really, really hard.

219
00:09:00,616 --> 00:09:03,178
And so that's how I felt.

220
00:09:03,178 --> 00:09:04,719
I had still my imposter syndrome.

221
00:09:04,719 --> 00:09:07,401
I felt totally out of place, but I was happy.

222
00:09:07,401 --> 00:09:09,002
And everyone else behind me was happy too

223
00:09:09,002 --> 00:09:11,043
because, well, we're dealing with the shit together.

224
00:09:11,043 --> 00:09:14,385
So I thought I figured it out.

225
00:09:14,385 --> 00:09:15,446
I know how to do art direction.

226
00:09:15,446 --> 00:09:16,127
I need to be happy,

227
00:09:16,127 --> 00:09:19,489
and I don't care that I don't know anything.

